{
  "description": "Prompt-span I/O contract for the WebhookRunner in BOTH languages: TS prompt-core/src/webhook-runner.ts and Python prompt_core/webhook_runner.py. The RUNNER (never executors) records `agentmark.input` (the formatted messages as {role, content} pairs, JSON-serialized) on the prompt span right after format(), and `agentmark.output` after the event stream drains \u2014 in BOTH streaming and non-streaming modes. The span ends when the stream drains (or the run returns), never when the executor's lazy iterable is created; ending early runs the model outside the span and splits model spans into a separate trace. Trace-level I/O derivation reads the root span's input/output first, so these attributes are what make trace I/O correct end-to-end. `expected.input` is compared as parsed JSON (TS and Python JSON spacing differs); `expected.output` is compared raw when a string, as parsed JSON otherwise; null means the attribute must be ABSENT. `throws: true` means the non-streaming run must reject/raise after emitting its observation. Changing any expectation is a cross-language tracing-contract break \u2014 update both runners and this file together. Additionally pinned: the runner stamps `gen_ai.request.model` (from frontmatter, expected.model) on every span at start, and `gen_ai.usage.input_tokens`/`output_tokens` (integers, from the finish event's usage \u2014 expected.usage as {input, output}, null = both absent) after drain.",
  "cases": [
    {
      "name": "non-streaming text: input + output recorded on the prompt span",
      "kind": "text",
      "shouldStream": false,
      "messages": [
        {
          "role": "system",
          "content": "be brief"
        },
        {
          "role": "user",
          "content": "hi"
        }
      ],
      "events": [
        {
          "type": "text-delta",
          "text": "hel"
        },
        {
          "type": "text-delta",
          "text": "lo"
        },
        {
          "type": "finish",
          "reason": "stop",
          "usage": {
            "inputTokens": 7,
            "outputTokens": 11
          }
        }
      ],
      "expected": {
        "input": [
          {
            "role": "system",
            "content": "be brief"
          },
          {
            "role": "user",
            "content": "hi"
          }
        ],
        "output": "hello",
        "model": "test",
        "usage": {
          "input": 7,
          "output": 11
        }
      },
      "throws": false
    },
